<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Posted this on the vault also....<P>Ok, wanted to get feedback. I have an idea that could possibly help give substance to the matter line, and make all 3 of our spec paths viable...<P>Right now if you spec heavy mind you get even con Pets to deal damage, and you get good crowd control.<P>Speccing body gives you decent DD and an AOE Root.<P>If you spec heavy matter you have only the DOT to rely on really. Too high (like to get the highest Spec DOT) and you lose the ability to keep even con pets, and your DD will suffer. Your CC options will also be more limited.<P>So what if a new charm line were added into matter? Charm undead. They don't have minds, so the mind line would not fit, but in the matter line you are taking control of their raw matter, so thematically it could fit.<P>Then with a high matter spec you would have undead pets (which are plentiful, but very vulnerable to certain damage types), some good DOTs, and some debuffs to help the pets.You can augment the Undead pet and DOT with some CC, or with some nice DD. <P>If you try to keep undead and living pets at 100% for most of your career (high mind and matter) your Root and raw Dd will be forfeit.<P>What does everyone think?<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
