<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
At the moment I am a Matter specced Sorcerer and I xp just fine.<P>A pet would be an advantage but not really needed.<P>Both DOT's and one DD+Snare will usually Drop yellow cons with ease.  Right now my DD+Snare at level 27 and 25 in matter does 169 to a yellow con and both DOT's, stacked, do 500 - 550 damage.<P>The best benefit would be to make that DD+Snare a PBAOE DD+Snare, it would make perfect sense.<P>I could stack the DOT's, run a little bit.  When the DOT's wear off I could PBAOE and if the mob does not die, I could run because of the snare effect then re-aply my spec DOT.<P>This would make the matter line very viable.  At the moment I just don't see the point in a ranged DD+Snare when my DOT's break the Snare.  That is why the PBAOE would be much better.  Especially since the mobs will be almost dead by the time they get to me.  It would also give us a AOE attack in which we don't have.<P>That is just my two cents but being one of the few Matter Sorcerers I think I know a little bit about the line.<P>--------------------<P>Cenergy 50th Smite Cleric<BR>Tuthican 36th Sword/Board<BR>Blemish 26th Matter Sorc<BR>Googley pet minstrel
