<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Has promise, but if played correctly (& under ideal circumstances (which is what we usually require for success), it could be quite overpowering.<P>Imagine this:<P>- See Troll.<BR>- Cast mid-level spec DOT doing around 500+ total damage.<BR>- Start running away.<BR>- Send in Level 50 Templar to beat on troll.<BR>- Send in Level 50 Cythraeth (semi-invisible)to nuke troll.<BR>- Kite as long as you feel necessary.<BR>- Turn & cast level 45 Lifedrain for 250-300 damage.<BR>- Hit troll with staff for 10 damage.<BR>- /em laugh at troll.<BR>- Hit troll with staff for 10 damage.<BR>- /em laugh at troll.<BR>- Quickcast level 45 Lifedrain for 250-300 damage & full heal.<BR>- /salute to troll.  /bow to troll.<BR>- Be on your merry way.<P>This allow for some potentially fearsome kiting that will really piss people off.  If two enemies happen by, we would still have our level 50 base mez to hold one down for a minute+.  There is a tradeoff in that it will be a major pain in the butt to find 2 good pets...and it will be even worse if you die & have to find them again, but the shouts of NERF SORCERERS will still be heard across the land the first time some Uber-Middy gets owned by a skinny sorcerer dual-wielding Level 50 pets.  AND, if a sorcerer decided to forgo their mind line all together (which is not unreasonable considering the fact that we dont seem to have a prayer of getting compensation for our mind losses), a person could possibly have 2 solid damage lines (DD in body & DOT in matter) PLUS a Level 50 Pet.  Thats a lot of damage coming at someone.<P>Again...not that I really see it as overpowered, considering all the downsides; however it COULD be overpowered & would likely be perceived as overpowered which would put us right back where we started.  Besides...I think we still need the undead charm in our mind line anyway.<P>--------------------<P>Palomides / Alat-Seldi<BR>Mezmo - Level 50 Sorcerer<BR>Siege - Level 32 Armsman<BR>Tagalong - Level 24 Full-Enhance Cleric<BR>